{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:15:22.095777+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ce907a77bdc824b30f8d9cc6bce388af0342e3fe)", "id": "lc_ae2467d4-eadc-4e40-b695-3aac2f023197"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport Logout from \"../components/auth/Logout\";\nimport Center from \"../components/utils/Center\";\n\nconst Home = (props) => {\n  useEffect(() => {}, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n  return (\n    <Center>\n      <Logout />\n    </Center>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Home;\n", "id": "lc_cf061cb5-d705-4484-854d-ff1ea60731cf"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0b249fea-9c19-4def-977d-fd6930a0d079", "tool_call_id": "call_623d4e9f46624a81bc88c1a2", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:15:22.095889+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 5ff2a77dcd6c2b34f7c51407ef2e793c6cda06a1)", "id": "lc_f540056f-bb1b-4beb-9672-e81d2b906064"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { Box, Tab, Tabs } from \"@mui/material\";\nimport React from \"react\";\nimport { useSearchParams } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport AuthContainer from \"../components/auth/AuthContainer\";\nimport Center from \"../components/utils/Center\";\n\nconst tabIdToURL = {\n  0: \"login\",\n  1: \"register\",\n};\n\nconst Login = (props) => {\n  // getting and setting URL params\n  const [searchParams, setSearchParams] = useSearchParams();\n\n  // get action from URL\n  const action = searchParams.get(\"action\") || \"login\";\n\n  // used to set initial state\n  let indexFromUrl = 0;\n  if (action === \"register\") {\n    indexFromUrl = 1;\n  }\n\n  // handle Tab Panel\n  const [value, setValue] = React.useState(indexFromUrl);\n\n  const handleChange = (event, newValue) => {\n    setValue(newValue);\n    const action = tabIdToURL[newValue];\n    setSearchParams({ action });\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <Center height={90}>\n      <Box\n        display={\"flex\"}\n        alignItems={\"center\"}\n        flexDirection={\"column\"}\n        boxShadow={2}\n        margin={3}\n      >\n        <Box sx={{ borderBottom: 1, borderColor: \"divider\", width: \"100%\" }}>\n          <Tabs value={value} onChange={handleChange} variant=\"fullWidth\">\n            <Tab sx={{ px: { lg: 20, xs: 6 } }} label=\"Login\" />\n            <Tab sx={{ px: { lg: 16, xs: 6 } }} label=\"Register\" />\n          </Tabs>\n        </Box>\n        {/* login */}\n        <TabPanel value={value} index={0}>\n          <AuthContainer />\n        </TabPanel>\n        {/* register */}\n        <TabPanel value={value} index={1}>\n          <AuthContainer />\n        </TabPanel>\n      </Box>\n    </Center>\n  );\n};\n\nconst TabPanel = ({ children, value, index }) => {\n  return (\n    <div role=\"tabpanel\" hidden={value !== index}>\n      {value === index && (\n        <Box sx={{ p: 3 }}>\n          <>{children}</>\n        </Box>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Login;\n", "id": "lc_39ce3a0e-19a4-426f-b411-d8db96efa9cf"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c6940e2c-6039-421f-bc35-a5c18ab78ac4", "tool_call_id": "call_2456bd78bf854b9da0220f6b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:15:32.753741+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed to give you a complete answer. Here's the breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## How Routing Is Configured\n\nThis is a **Create React App template** that uses **`react-router-dom` v6** for client-side routing with **Firebase Authentication** for access control.\n\n### The Routing Architecture\n\n**1. Route definitions** are centralized in **`src/config/routes.js`**:\n\n| Route Path | Component | `protected` flag |\n|---|---|---|\n| `\"\"` (root `/`) | `Home` | `true` ✅ |\n| `\"/login\"` | `Login` | `false` 🔓 |\n\n**2. Route rendering** happens in **`src/App.js`**, which iterates over the `routes` array and conditionally wraps each route's component:\n\n```jsx\n<Route\n  key={index}\n  path={route.path}\n  element={\n    route.protected ? (\n      <AuthChecker>\n        <route.component />\n      </AuthChecker>\n    ) : (\n      <route.component />\n    )\n  }\n/>\n```\n\nIf `route.protected` is `true`, the component is wrapped in an `<AuthChecker>` guard. Otherwise, it renders directly.\n\n**3. Auth guard** is implemented in **`src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`**:\n\n```jsx\nconst AuthChecker = ({ children }) => {\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!auth.currentUser) {\n      navigate(\"/login\");  // redirects unauthenticated users to /login\n    }\n  }, []);\n  return <>{children}</>;\n};\n```\n\nIt checks Firebase's `auth.currentUser`. If no user is logged in, it redirects to `/login`.\n\n---\n\n### Which Route Requires Authentication?\n\n- **`/` (Home page)** — This route is **protected** (`protected: true`). It is wrapped in `<AuthChecker>`, so only authenticated users can access it. Unauthenticated visitors are redirected to `/login`.\n\n### Which Route Is Public?\n\n- **`/login` (Login screen)** — This route is **public** (`protected: false`). Anyone can access it without authentication. It provides Login and Register tabs using Firebase Google authentication (via `AuthContainer`).\n\n### Additional Notes\n\n- On app startup (`App.js`), the app listens to Firebase's `onAuthStateChanged` and shows a loading spinner until the auth state is resolved — this prevents a flash of the login page for already-authenticated users.\n- The `BrowserRouter` uses `process.env.PUBLIC_URL` as its `basename`, supporting deployment to sub-paths (e.g., GitHub Pages via `gh-pages`).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 569, "prompt_tokens": 11966, "total_tokens": 12535, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 20, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11136, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008961696, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0004011396, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00049503}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863322-jWsbsNGpPxDLlYuQzBDN", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b9-c7f1-7dd0-9041-d37653397c3d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11966, "output_tokens": 569, "total_tokens": 12535, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11136}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 20}}}}]}}}
